1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,500
JPMorgan Chase just did something most
businesses haven't woken up to yet.

2
00:00:04,500 --> 00:00:11,000
They reclassified AI from R and D
to core infrastructure.

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:15,500
Same line item as the data centers.
Same line item as the trading systems.

4
00:00:15,500 --> 00:00:19,000
Not an experiment anymore,
a utility.

5
00:00:19,000 --> 00:00:24,000
The 2026 number is
19.8 billion dollars.

6
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,500
Two thousand staff
working on AI full-time.

7
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:34,000
Now if you're running a small or medium
business in Singapore, your first reaction

8
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,000
is probably "that's a bank,
that's not me."

9
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,000
And I want to push back on that.
Because the lesson isn't the dollar amount.

10
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:45,500
The lesson is the
category change.

11
00:00:45,500 --> 00:00:52,000
Here's what changed. For five years, AI
sat in the innovation budget.

12
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:55,500
The CIO had a sandbox.
The COO had a pilot project.

13
00:00:55,500 --> 00:01:01,000
The CFO had a line that said
"experimental, review next year."

14
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:06,500
That line is gone now. AI is now sitting
next to the electricity bill.

15
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:09,500
It's sitting next to the lease.

16
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:15,000
It's a fixed cost of running the business,
because the alternative is

17
00:01:15,000 --> 00:01:18,500
your competitor has it
and you don't.

18
00:01:18,500 --> 00:01:24,000
So what does that mean for a 30-person
company in Tanjong Pagar?

19
00:01:24,000 --> 00:01:28,000
Or a 12-person logistics
firm in Tuas?

20
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:33,000
Three things. And I want you to actually
do them this month, not bookmark them.

21
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:38,000
One. Stop calling it AI.
Start calling it staff.

22
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:43,500
Every time you write "AI" in a budget
line, it gets pushed to next quarter.

23
00:01:43,500 --> 00:01:49,000
Every time you write "automation"
or "junior analyst capacity"

24
00:01:49,000 --> 00:01:53,500
or "after-hours coverage,"
it gets approved.

25
00:01:53,500 --> 00:02:00,000
JPMorgan didn't suddenly have 19 billion
dollars of AI budget appear.

26
00:02:00,000 --> 00:02:05,500
They moved existing budget from headcount,
from consulting, from manual ops.

27
00:02:05,500 --> 00:02:10,000
The number is big because
the savings were big.

28
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:15,000
Look at your last three months
of manual work.

29
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:20,000
Reconciliation. Quote generation.
Customer email triage.

30
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:23,500
That's your AI budget.
It's already in your P and L.

31
00:02:23,500 --> 00:02:27,000
It's just hiding in payroll.

32
00:02:27,000 --> 00:02:32,000
Two. Pick the boring task,
not the impressive one.

33
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:37,000
Every founder I talk to wants
to build the AI chatbot.

34
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:42,500
The AI sales assistant. The AI something
that goes on the homepage.

35
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:45,000
Don't.

36
00:02:45,000 --> 00:02:50,500
JPMorgan's biggest AI win this year
was internal.

37
00:02:50,500 --> 00:02:55,000
Agents that read documents
and pre-fill forms.

38
00:02:55,000 --> 00:02:59,000
That's it. Boring.
Massive ROI.

39
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:04,500
Your equivalent: invoice scanning.
Receipt categorisation.

40
00:03:04,500 --> 00:03:07,500
Vendor email summarisation.

41
00:03:07,500 --> 00:03:13,000
Pick one. Ship it in 14 days.
Measure the hours saved.

42
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:18,000
That's the case for AI in your business,
not a press release.

43
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:23,500
Three. Build for portability,
not for a vendor.

44
00:03:23,500 --> 00:03:30,000
JPMorgan can lock into OpenAI or Anthropic
and switch in a weekend

45
00:03:30,000 --> 00:03:33,500
because they built abstractions.

46
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:39,500
Most SMBs build directly against one API
and then can't move when prices change

47
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:43,000
or models get deprecated.

48
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:48,500
Use a thin wrapper. Whether it's LangChain,
LiteLLM, or a 50-line Python file

49
00:03:48,500 --> 00:03:54,000
you wrote yourself, make sure swapping
models is a one-line change.

50
00:03:54,000 --> 00:03:59,000
The AI vendor war is going
to get ugly in 2027.

51
00:03:59,000 --> 00:04:02,500
Don't be locked in.

52
00:04:02,500 --> 00:04:08,500
If you want me to look at where AI fits
in your specific business

53
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:13,500
and what the 14-day win looks like for you,
the link is in the description.

54
00:04:13,500 --> 00:04:19,500
The companies that move now spend
the next two years compounding.

55
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:25,500
The companies that wait are going to spend
the next two years explaining to their board

56
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:28,500
why they didn't.

57
00:04:28,500 --> 00:04:32,000
See you in the next one.
